	(217,2,'2014-04-14 17:19:10','2014-04-14 21:19:10','\r\nWhether you’re graduating high school now or trying to attend cosmetology school despite your current job keeping you busy, we know a weekday education schedule isn’t for everyone. At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, you can find the cosmetology classes you need held during weekdays, nights and weekends. \r\n\r\nOur full-time day, full-time evening and part-time evening programs provide students the flexibility they need to complete their studies on-time and on-budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Day: </strong>\r\nMonday through Friday, 8:45 a.m. to 3:15 p.m.\r\n30 hours per week, approximately 34 to 36 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\nSaturday: 9:00 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.\r\n25 hours per week, approximately 40 to 43 weeks\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Part-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\n20 hours per week, approximately 50 to 54 weeks\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//admissions/tuition-financial-aid/\" title=\"Tuition & Financial Aid\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition</a> is the same regardless of the program schedule you choose - we want you to choose the schedule that will provide you the opportunity to succeed! \r\n\r\n','Course Schedule','','inherit','open','open','','126-revision-v1','','','2014-04-14 17:19:10','2014-04-14 21:19:10','',126,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/126-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
