	(210,2,'2014-04-14 17:11:20','2014-04-14 21:11:20','The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is committed to instructing students in the skills and principles of Cosmetology and Nail Technology. Our curriculum is designed to prepare students to successfully pass the New York Department of State and Appearance Enhancement and Nail Technology examinations, earn their cosmetology licenses and help them begin long-term careers within our industry.\r\n\r\n<h3>Why Cosmetology?</h3>\r\n\r\nAt Orlo, we are passionate about cosmetology, and our students are, too. Working in the cosmetology industry allows us to make personal connections with people, surround ourselves with creative minds, and learn and experiment with new techniques throughout our careers. The services learned in beauty school are always in demand, ensuring the skills you develop today will be valued for years to come.\r\n\r\nIn addition to learning the arts and sciences of hair, skin and nails, career opportunities available to the licensed cosmetologist include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hairdresser</li>\r\n	<li>Nail Technician</li>\r\n	<li>Esthetician</li>\r\n	<li>Beauticians</li>\r\n	<li>Salon Manager</li>\r\n	<li>Platform Artist</li>\r\n	<li>Sales Representative</li>\r\n	<li>Consulting</li>\r\n	<li>Make-up Artist</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n… and many more!\r\n<h3>The Cosmetology Program</h3>\r\nTo graduate, students must satisfactorily complete the 1000-hour Cosmetology curriculum in accordance with our Satisfactory Progress Policy and satisfy all monetary obligations to the school. Graduates then receive a diploma, which states that they have successfully completed the required 1000 hours of training and are eligible for a temporary cosmetology license. They are then qualified to take the New York State Licensing Exam.','Program','','inherit','open','open','','6-revision-v1','','','2014-04-14 17:11:20','2014-04-14 21:11:20','',6,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/6-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(211,2,'2014-04-14 17:11:47','2014-04-14 21:11:47','The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is an independent, privately-owned cosmetology school devoted to educating new cosmetology industry professionals. Our students move on to a variety of careers, from working as hairdressers, makeup artists and estheticians to owning independent beauty salons and representing major industry product companies.\r\n\r\nAt our cosmetology school, we’re interested not only in the creative aspects of cosmetology but the business of our industry, as well. Our students are prepared to start their own careers, and if they choose, to start their own businesses. While they learn how to style the looks of the individuals in front of them, they also learn how to attract new clients and how to retain them.\r\n\r\n<h3>There are a lot of beauty schools - why Orlo?</h3>\r\n\r\nWe know the decision about which beauty school to attend can be difficult, but we promise you this -\r\n\r\n<i>We’re passionate about what we teach, and you can tell that as soon as you walk in our doors.</i>\r\n\r\nEvery day, we get to see new students pair their passion for beauty and design with skills that will help them succeed. Throughout our history, we’ve educated thousands of students who have received their cosmetology licenses from the New York State Board of Cosmetology and gone on to bright futures, and we look forward to many more years of education as a top beauty school ahead of us.','About','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-v1','','','2014-04-14 17:11:47','2014-04-14 21:11:47','',4,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(214,2,'2014-04-14 17:17:06','2014-04-14 21:17:06','The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology’s 1000-hour Cosmetology curriculum prepares students for the many responsibilities faced by industry professionals such as estheticians and hairdressers. Our courses are presented by a combination of lecture, demonstration and student practice, with approximately 680 hours devoted to practical application. Students demonstrate their knowledge through theory and practical exams and their completion of required clinic activities.\n\nIntroduce yourself to the units our students study at Orlo every day, and then explore the various course schedules available to full and part-time students.\n\n<h4>Professional Requirements (24 hours)</h4>\nStudy budgeting, time management techniques, client communication tips, ethics, image and more to prepare you for work in a professional setting. \n\n<h4>Safety & Health (26 hours)</h4>\nBe educated on the principles of infection and prevention, precautions and procedures that are necessary for both cosmetologists and their clients. \n\n<h4>Anatomy & Physiology (15 hours)</h4>\nLearn about the human body to understand why your nutrition, exercise and health conditions can affect your appearance. Study how body systems such as the circulatory system, digestive system and respiratory system can influence the health and appearance of skin, hair and nails. \n\n<h4>Hair Analysis (10 hours)</h4>\nStudy the properties of the hair and scalp. Learn about the structure and chemical composition of hair, the causes of hair growth and loss and how to analyze the hair of your clients. \n\n<h4>Hair & Scalp Disorders & Diseases (10 hours)</h4>\nStudy and learn to identify the many disorders of the hair and scalp, including the technical terms for abnormal hair growth, splits ends, brittle hair, beaded hair and dandruff, among other conditions. \n\n<h4>Chemistry as Applied to Cosmetology (5 hours)</h4>\nWhy study chemistry? Cosmetologists must be able to use professional products safely and effectively, and each of these products contains chemicals. A background in chemistry helps you solve problems that may occur with chemical services provided to clients. \n\n<h4>Shampoo, Rinses, Conditioners & Treatments (30 hours)</h4>\nShampooing - it’s more than just washing hair. At this time, you can also identify and address hair and scalp conditions that require solutions. Here we explore the various shampoos, conditioners and other treatments available to treat clients with specific hair-care needs, and we walk through each process with practical applications. \n\n<h4>Haircutting & Shaping (175 hours)</h4>\nBefore you can begin to cut hair, you must be able to identify the best haircuts for the shape of your client’s head. Study the basic principles of haircutting and shaping, including handling various hair densities and textures, managing client consultations, and managing the various tools associated with haircutting. Classroom study will be followed by practical application. \n\n<h4>Hairstyling (245 hours)</h4>\nPractice techniques such as finger waving, pin curling, roller setting and hair wrapping. Learn about hair pressing, long hair techniques, and blowdry styling techniques, and combine these techniques to achieve results your future clients will seek.  \n\n<h4>Chemical Restructuring (180 hours)</h4>\nChemical restructuring allows stylists to change the texture of the clients’ hair in order to achieve the desired appearance. Study the various chemical texture services and practice their application.\n\n<h4>Haircoloring & Lightening (180 hours)</h4>\nUnderstand how porosity and melanin affect hair color, and learn how to successfully lighten, darken and highlight hair. Work includes the study of hair color formulation, gray hair coverage, color correction and more.  \n\n<h4>Nail Care & Procedures (40 hours)</h4>\nFrom manicuring and pedicuring to nail tips, wraps and enhancements, study and practice everything you need to know to work as a nail technician. \n\nSkin Care & Procedures (60 hours)</h4>\nPeople aren’t just concerned about their hair - they’re worried about their skin and make-up, too. Study and practice skin care, facial services, make-up application and hair removal.  \n','Curriculum','','inherit','open','open','','124-autosave-v1','','','2014-04-14 17:17:06','2014-04-14 21:17:06','',124,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/124-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
