	(272,2,'2014-04-15 12:54:03','2014-04-15 16:54:03','At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, we want every person who walks through our beauty school\'s doors to feel welcome. Our school is always full of cosmetology students, instructors, guests, family members and friends, and that’s the way we like it. And once you graduate? We want our Orlo <a href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//alumni/\" title=\"Alumni\" target=\"_blank\">alumni</a> to keep in touch and remain apart of our community for many, many years. \r\n\r\nWe’re proud to be a part of the Capital Region community, and we enjoy <a href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//community/local-involvement/\" title=\"Local Involvement\" target=\"_blank\">being involved</a> in regional activities, from fundraisers to fashion shows. And we love when our neighbors come to us – our <a href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//community/student-salon-services/\" title=\"Student Salon Services\" target=\"_blank\">student salon services </a> are available throughout the week, and more visitors are always welcome!\r\n','Community','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2014-04-15 12:54:03','2014-04-15 16:54:03','',11,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(276,2,'2014-04-15 12:56:59','2014-04-15 16:56:59','Whether you’re graduating high school now or trying to attend cosmetology school despite your current job keeping you busy, we know a weekday education schedule isn’t for everyone. At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, you can find the cosmetology classes you need held during weekdays, nights and weekends.\r\n\r\nOur full-time day, full-time evening and part-time evening programs provide students the flexibility they need to complete their studies on-time and on-budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Day: </strong>\r\nMonday through Friday, 8:45 a.m. to 3:15 p.m.\r\n30 hours per week, approximately 34 to 36 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\nSaturday: 9:00 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.\r\n25 hours per week, approximately 40 to 43 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Part-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\n20 hours per week, approximately 50 to 54 weeks\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Tuition &amp; Financial Aid\" href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//admissions/tuition-financial-aid/\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition</a> is the same regardless of the program schedule you choose - we want you to choose the schedule that will provide you the opportunity to succeed!\r\n\r\n[accordion title=\"School Holidays\"] No classes are scheduled at Orlo on the following days each year:\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>New Year’s Day</li>\r\n	<li>Martin Luther King Day</li>\r\n	<li>Presidents’ Day</li>\r\n	<li>Memorial Day</li>\r\n	<li>Fourth of July (entire week)</li>\r\n	<li>Labor Day</li>\r\n	<li>Columbus Day</li>\r\n	<li>Veterans Day</li>\r\n	<li>Thanksgiving (two days)</li>\r\n	<li>Christmas (one week)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/accordion][accordion title=\"Unexpected Closures\"] In cases of circumstances such as weather and natural disasters, school closure announcements will be available on our website. Additional notifications will be made by personal phone call, radio/TV announcements or on <a href=\"http://https://www.facebook.com/theorloschool\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a> as applicable.\r\n[/accordion]','Course Schedule','','inherit','open','open','','126-revision-v1','','','2014-04-15 12:56:59','2014-04-15 16:56:59','',126,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/126-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(510,1,'2014-09-23 13:26:24','2014-09-23 17:26:24','The Orlo School of Hair Design &amp; Cosmetology had the pleasure of catching up with 2009 graduate and Alumni standout, Lauren Sebert.  As an Education Major at Russell Sage College, she realized that the job demand for teaching and student loans were not looking good.  She knew she would be in competition with 500 other applicants looking for a job. With her passion for the beauty industry in combination of her family’s support, Lauren decided to pursue Cosmetology instead of a Master’s Degree.\n\nChoosing Orlo was a no brainer.  As a Receptionist at the Hair-Em Salon in Ravena her co-workers went to Orlo and highly recommended it.  Her favorite memory of Orlo was working on the Senior Floor and learning from her favorite Instructor, Ms. Siebles.  There on the Senior Floor is where she fell in love with interacting with the public and practicing on friends.\n\nAfter graduation, she started as a full time stylist at the Hair-Em Salon.  Then an amazing opportunity happened; the owner of the Hair-Em Salon retired and offered the business to Lauren!  At 23 years young, Lauren was a successful business owner and savvy Stylist.  The Hair-Em is going on its fifth year under Lauren’s strong ownership, their salon, in the small town of Ravena gets local clients as well as people who travel all the way from Clifton Park and Kingston!  The talented team specializes in cutting and coloring.  As a busy Stylist and Salon Owner, Lauren balances her business and adorable family.  She utilizes a salon computer system that allows her to work from home in addition to inside the salon with her great team.  She couldn’t stress enough how awesome, trustworthy and well educated her team was.  Our very own Orlo Instructor, Ms. Jackie Bushnell, is a proud employee.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe best thing about being a hairstylist for Lauren is that the industry is pretty flexible, it’s not your typical nine to five job.  You can have a family, make your own schedule, be creative and free-spirited.  For the talented Lauren it fit her personality and lifetstyle!  We love Lauren!\n\nCome visit the lovely and talented team at <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Hair-Em-Salon/137550972979928\">The Hair-Em Salon</a>, a full-service family salon conveniently located on 152 Main Street in Ravena, New York.  They offer hair care, nail care, tanning, waxing, wedding and prom packages.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/10264139_679328319467_8981207446077766177_o.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-468\" src=\"http://www.theorloschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/10264139_679328319467_8981207446077766177_o-300x194.jpg\" alt=\"10264139_679328319467_8981207446077766177_o\" width=\"300\" height=\"194\" /></a>','Alumni Spotlight: Lauren Sebert, Stylist/Salon Owner at Hair-Em Salon','','inherit','open','closed','','466-autosave-v1','','','2014-09-23 13:26:24','2014-09-23 17:26:24','',466,'http://www.theorloschool.com/2014/09/466-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(298,2,'2014-04-15 13:31:39','2014-04-15 17:31:39','<div id=\"lipsum\">\r\n\r\nWe love the cosmetology industry, and we love introducing new students to the opportunities it provides us all. If you share our passion, we invite you to explore our employment opportunities.\r\n\r\nBelow you’ll find our current job opportunities at The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology. Explore the descriptions and (link: EMAIL US) your résumé and cover letter, along with any other materials you think would give us an understanding of your talents and strength.\r\n\r\nDon’t see a position listed now that’s right for you but think you can make a difference at our cosmetology school? Reach out to us at any time to introduce yourself, and we’ll keep you in mind for future opportunities.\r\n\r\n</div>','Employment','','inherit','open','open','','175-revision-v1','','','2014-04-15 13:31:39','2014-04-15 17:31:39','',175,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/175-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(299,2,'2014-04-15 15:13:00','2014-04-15 19:13:00','<div id=\"lipsum\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The Capital Region is full of exciting opportunities, and The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is right in the middle of it all. With shopping destinations uptown, culture and night-life downtown, and fine dining options spread across the region, it’s hard to get bored.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">[accordion title=\"Dining\"]</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Even in short walking distance, you’ll find popular lunch spots like Pepper Jack’s, and on tough mornings, you can fuel up right around the corner at Dunkin Donuts. Branching out, you’ll find many hidden gems in the area, like New World Bistro on Delaware Avenue, and popular favorites like The Cheesecake Factory in Colonie Center. Central Avenue boasts many nearby options as well, such as Ichiban and El Mariachi. Whatever you’re in the mood for, Albany is sure to have it.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> [/accordion]</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">[accordion title=\"Entertainment\"]</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The Capital Region is home to a variety of festivals and concerts all year long. From Tulip Fest in the spring to Pearl Palooza in the fall, there’s always something to look forward to. Even in the winter, you can get out and go ice-skating at Empire State Plaza or visit the nearby Adirondacks for many outdoor activities! Many big names come to perform in the area and surrounding local venues. Catch shows at Proctor’s or the Palace Theatre, or join your friends for a night out on Lark Street.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> [/accordion]</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">[accordion title=\"Shopping\"]</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The Capital Region offers premier shopping at Crossgates Mall and Colonie Center, both less than five miles from our school. Wolf Road, Central Ave and Western Ave provide all the stores you need for everyday necessities.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">  [/accordion]</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">[accordion title=\"Transportation\"]</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Capital District Transit Authority (CDTA) provides an easy and inexpensive route system to get you where you need to go. Buses connect the entire region, including services extending north to Saratoga. Orlo is located four miles from the Albany-Rensselaer Amtrak rail station and six miles from the Albany International Airport.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> [/accordion]</p>\n\n</div>','City Highlights','','inherit','open','open','','142-revision-v1','','','2014-04-15 15:13:00','2014-04-15 19:13:00','',142,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/04/142-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(305,1,'2014-05-01 14:36:12','2014-05-01 18:36:12','Interested in applying for The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology’s program?\r\n\r\nWe’d love to meet you and discuss how our cosmetology school can help you move toward a successful career!\r\n\r\nFill out the form below with the preliminary information we need to start your application process. Once we review what you\'ve submitted, we\'ll move forward with in-person interviews, and finally, work with you to complete the full application process.\r\n\r\nFORM NEEDED - PRELIMINARY INFO FIELDS FROM CLIENT REQUIRED (AGE? ADDRESS? LEVEL OF EXPERIENCE?)','Apply Now','','inherit','open','open','','15-revision-v1','','','2014-05-01 14:36:12','2014-05-01 18:36:12','',15,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/15-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(308,1,'2014-05-05 10:04:49','2014-05-05 14:04:49','<strong>The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology</strong> is accredited by the National Accrediting Commission of Career Arts and Sciences, which is recognized by the United States Department of Education as the official accrediting agency for Hairdressing and Cosmetology schools.\r\n\r\nNational Accrediting Commission of Career Arts &amp; Sciences (NACCAS)\r\n4401 Ford Avenue, Suite 1300\r\nAlexandria, VA 22302 - (703) 600-7600\r\n<h3>Orlo is licensed by:</h3>\r\nThe New York State Education Department\r\nOffice of Adult Career and Continuing Education Services (ACCES)\r\nBureau of Proprietary School Supervision\r\n99 Washington Avenue, Room 1613 OCP\r\nAlbany, NY 12234 - (518) 474-3969\r\n<h3>Orlo is approved by:</h3>\r\nUSDOE: United States Department of Education, authorizing participation in Title IV Federal Student Financial Assistance Programs.\r\n\r\nVA: New York State Division of Veteran’s Affairs.\r\n\r\nACCES-VR: New York State Education Department Office of Adult Career Continuing Education Services-Vocational Rehabilitation.\r\n\r\nNYHESC: Eligible Institution under the New York State Higher Education Services Corporation.\r\n<h3>Orlo is affiliated with:</h3>\r\nNYDOS: New York Department of State\r\n\r\nAACS: American Association of Cosmetology Schools\r\n\r\nCEA: Cosmetology Educators of America\r\n\r\nNYSBSA: New York State Beauty School Association\r\n\r\nBBB: Better Business Bureau\r\n\r\nNASFAA: National Association of Student Financial Aid Administrators','Accreditation','','inherit','open','open','','46-revision-v1','','','2014-05-05 10:04:49','2014-05-05 14:04:49','',46,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/46-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(309,1,'2014-05-05 10:27:41','2014-05-05 14:27:41','Applying to colleges can be an exciting time, even if it’s a bit nerve-wracking. At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, we know that choosing your cosmetology school is a big decision, and we understand if you’re a bit nervous about it. Our admissions team is prepared to answer any questions you may have about our beauty school, our program or our applications process at any time!\r\n\r\nOrlo accepts students on a rolling basis. <i>New classes begin every month!</i>\r\n<h3>Cosmetology Program Admission Requirements</h3>\r\nEach applicant must submit the following documents:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Proof of age (the applicant must be 17 years of age) documented by a driver\'s license, birth certificate, passport or other State or Federal ID</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of a high school diploma or GED</li>\r\n	<li>$100.00 non-refundable registration fee</li>\r\n	<li>All entrance documents (CLIENT MUST CONFIRM THIS LINE?)</li>\r\n	<li>Enrollment agreement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition, all applicants must attend an interview and have a tour of our school prior to admission.\r\n<h3>Transfer Student Admission Requirements</h3>\r\nOrlo does not recruit students already attending a school that offers a similar cosmetology program. It is our policy to discourage students from transferring beauty schools as it can be costly and may cause an interruption to the continuity of the student’s education.\r\n\r\nHowever, we understand when unforeseen circumstances or hardships may make it necessary to transfer. Relocation from another state or geographic area, inability to complete a vocational or high school program, etc., will be taken into consideration on a case-by-case basis.\r\n\r\nA maximum of 500 hours may be accepted from another recognized school. The transfer process cannot begin until we receive, by mail, an official transcript of hours and grades completed at the previous school. Potential transfer students must also provide documentation that meets our entrance requirements. A personal interview and examination to determine the number of hours that may be accepted must be completed before acceptance. Prospective transfer students will be responsible for all equipment and supplies needed to complete the examination, and the examination will cost $100.00.\r\n\r\nAn hourly rate of $10.30 per hour will be charged for the remaining hours needed to complete our program, plus the cost of kit, books, supplies needed and a $100.00 non-refundable registration fee.','Admissions','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2014-05-05 10:27:41','2014-05-05 14:27:41','',8,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(310,1,'2014-05-05 13:40:48','2014-05-05 17:40:48','Do you have questions for our admissions team? Or, would you like to visit The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology? You can reach our admissions team through the form below.\r\n\r\nIf you\'d like to visit our cosmetology school, let us arrange a personal tour for you! We’ll show you around the classrooms and student salon at our cosmetology school, and sit with you to learn more about you, introduce ourselves and our program, answer any questions you may have about beauty school or the cosmetology industry, and discuss the admissions process. Tours are available Monday through Saturday - contact us today to schedule yours!\r\n\r\nWe’ll respond shortly to confirm your visit or answer any questions you may have about our program, teachers, students and school.','Contact Admissions','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-v1','','','2014-05-05 13:40:48','2014-05-05 17:40:48','',31,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/31-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(311,1,'2014-05-05 15:52:55','2014-05-05 19:52:55','At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, we want every person who walks through our beauty school\'s doors to feel welcome. Our school is always full of cosmetology students, instructors, guests, family members and friends, and that’s the way we like it. And once you graduate? We want our Orlo <a title=\"Alumni\" href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//alumni/\" target=\"_blank\">alumni</a> to keep in touch and remain apart of our community for many, many years.\r\n\r\nWe’re proud to be a part of the Capital Region community, and we enjoy <a title=\"Local Involvement\" href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//community/local-involvement/\" target=\"_blank\">being involved</a> in regional activities, from fundraisers to fashion shows. And we love when our neighbors come to us – our <a title=\"Student Salon Services\" href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//community/student-salon-services/\" target=\"_blank\">student salon services </a> are available throughout the week, and more visitors are always welcome!','Community','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2014-05-05 15:52:55','2014-05-05 19:52:55','',11,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(312,1,'2014-05-06 11:55:33','2014-05-06 15:55:33','The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology is committed to instructing students in the skills and principles of Cosmetology and Nail Technology. Our curriculum is designed to prepare students to successfully pass the New York Department of State and Appearance Enhancement and Nail Technology examinations, earn their cosmetology licenses and help them begin long-term careers within our industry.\r\n<h3>Why Cosmetology?</h3>\r\nAt Orlo, we are passionate about cosmetology, and our students are, too. Working in the cosmetology industry allows us to make personal connections with people, surround ourselves with creative minds, and learn and experiment with new techniques throughout our careers. The services learned in beauty school are always in demand, ensuring the skills you develop today will be valued for years to come.\r\n\r\nIn addition to learning the arts and sciences of hair, skin and nails, career opportunities available to the licensed cosmetologist include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hairdresser</li>\r\n	<li>Nail Technician</li>\r\n	<li>Esthetician</li>\r\n	<li>Beauticians</li>\r\n	<li>Salon Manager</li>\r\n	<li>Platform Artist</li>\r\n	<li>Sales Representative</li>\r\n	<li>Consulting</li>\r\n	<li>Make-up Artist</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n… and many more!\r\n<h3>The Cosmetology Program</h3>\r\nTo graduate, students must satisfactorily complete the 1000-hour Cosmetology <a title=\"Curriculum\" href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//program/curriculum/\" target=\"_blank\">curriculum</a> in accordance with our Satisfactory Progress Policy and satisfy all monetary obligations to the school. Graduates then receive a diploma, which states that they have successfully completed the required 1000 hours of training and are eligible for a temporary cosmetology license. They are then qualified to take the New York State Licensing Exam.','Program','','inherit','open','open','','6-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 11:55:33','2014-05-06 15:55:33','',6,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/6-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(313,1,'2014-05-06 11:59:08','2014-05-06 15:59:08','The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology’s 1000-hour Cosmetology curriculum prepares students for the many responsibilities faced by industry professionals such as estheticians and hairdressers. Our courses are presented by a combination of lecture, demonstration and student practice, with approximately 680 hours devoted to practical application. Students demonstrate their knowledge through theory and practical exams and their completion of required clinic activities.\r\n\r\nIntroduce yourself to the units our students study at Orlo every day, and then explore the various <a title=\"Course Schedule\" href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//program/course-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\">course schedules</a> available to full and part-time students.\r\n<h4>Professional Requirements (24 hours)</h4>\r\nStudy budgeting, time management techniques, client communication tips, ethics, image and more to prepare you for work in a professional setting.\r\n<h4>Safety &amp; Health (26 hours)</h4>\r\nBe educated on the principles of infection and prevention, precautions and procedures that are necessary for both cosmetologists and their clients.\r\n<h4>Anatomy &amp; Physiology (15 hours)</h4>\r\nLearn about the human body to understand why your nutrition, exercise and health conditions can affect your appearance. Study how body systems such as the circulatory system, digestive system and respiratory system can influence the health and appearance of skin, hair and nails.\r\n<h4>Hair Analysis (10 hours)</h4>\r\nStudy the properties of the hair and scalp. Learn about the structure and chemical composition of hair, the causes of hair growth and loss and how to analyze the hair of your clients.\r\n<h4>Hair &amp; Scalp Disorders &amp; Diseases (10 hours)</h4>\r\nStudy and learn to identify the many disorders of the hair and scalp, including the technical terms for abnormal hair growth, splits ends, brittle hair, beaded hair and dandruff, among other conditions.\r\n<h4>Chemistry as Applied to Cosmetology (5 hours)</h4>\r\nWhy study chemistry? Cosmetologists must be able to use professional products safely and effectively, and each of these products contains chemicals. A background in chemistry helps you solve problems that may occur with chemical services provided to clients.\r\n<h4>Shampoo, Rinses, Conditioners &amp; Treatments (30 hours)</h4>\r\nShampooing - it’s more than just washing hair. At this time, you can also identify and address hair and scalp conditions that require solutions. Here we explore the various shampoos, conditioners and other treatments available to treat clients with specific hair-care needs, and we walk through each process with practical applications.\r\n<h4>Haircutting &amp; Shaping (175 hours)</h4>\r\nBefore you can begin to cut hair, you must be able to identify the best haircuts for the shape of your client’s head. Study the basic principles of haircutting and shaping, including handling various hair densities and textures, managing client consultations, and managing the various tools associated with haircutting. Classroom study will be followed by practical application.\r\n<h4>Hairstyling (245 hours)</h4>\r\nPractice techniques such as finger waving, pin curling, roller setting and hair wrapping. Learn about hair pressing, long hair techniques, and blowdry styling techniques, and combine these techniques to achieve results your future clients will seek.\r\n<h4>Chemical Restructuring (180 hours)</h4>\r\nChemical restructuring allows stylists to change the texture of the clients’ hair in order to achieve the desired appearance. Study the various chemical texture services and practice their application.\r\n<h4>Haircoloring &amp; Lightening (180 hours)</h4>\r\nUnderstand how porosity and melanin affect hair color, and learn how to successfully lighten, darken and highlight hair. Work includes the study of hair color formulation, gray hair coverage, color correction and more.\r\n<h4>Nail Care &amp; Procedures (40 hours)</h4>\r\nFrom manicuring and pedicuring to nail tips, wraps and enhancements, study and practice everything you need to know to work as a nail technician.\r\n<h4>Skin Care &amp; Procedures (60 hours)</h4>\r\nPeople aren’t just concerned about their hair - they’re worried about their skin and make-up, too. Study and practice skin care, facial services, make-up application and hair removal.','Curriculum','','inherit','open','open','','124-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 11:59:08','2014-05-06 15:59:08','',124,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/05/124-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
