	(372,1,'2014-06-17 17:07:09','2014-06-17 21:07:09','Angela literally grew up in the beauty industry as the owners\' daughter. After receiving her BA from SUNY New Paltz in sociology and art, she decided to return to Albany to work in the family business. She loves the flexibility and variety that you get daily working in the industry. Angela also gets to incorporate her love of photography by doing photo shoots with the students.  Angela is a Director at The Orlo School, and in addition sheus she manages Studio Orlo, our Aveda salon in Niskayuna, NY. “The beauty industry is such a fun and rewarding industry to be a part of. We get to spend all day in an uplifting environment making other people feel good about themselves.”\n','Angela Caputo','Director/Owner','inherit','open','closed','','75-autosave-v1','','','2014-06-17 17:07:09','2014-06-17 21:07:09','',75,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/75-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(373,1,'2014-06-17 17:08:55','2014-06-17 21:08:55','Rick is the “patriarch” of the Orlo family. His first introduction to the beauty industry was in the early 1960s when he drove his Aunt Carmey to beauty school from Gloversville to Albany everyday. Was it all the pretty women, or was it the energy and excitement of the business that intrigued him the most? From that time on, he was hooked. After gaining experience in the salon as a licensed cosmetologist, he became engrossed in teaching cosmetology. At the time, Sassoon was becoming a household name, and Leo Passage was revolutionizing the way cosmetology was taught with his scientific approach to hairdressing. The industry was going through a transformation, and Rick was at the forefront. He became a platform artist for the Clairol Company and won numerous awards for his hair-cutting and hair-styling skills. He also trained several of his students to compete in local and national styling competitions.\n \nOver the years, Rick has learned the “ins and outs” of the beauty school business and all that the industry entails. Thousands of successful cosmetologists have graduated from his schools. After marrying Alice in 1984, they went into the beauty school business together, first with Colonna Beauty School where Rick had worked since the early 60’s. In 1995, they purchased The Orlo to provide a more convenient location for their students. Rick is now grooming his children, Angela and Andrew to hone their skills to carry on the tradition to the next generation. “Hairdressing and cosmetology have always been my passion and I take great pride in our many accomplished students who have gone on to have their own successful careers in the industry.”','Rick Caputo','Director/Owner','inherit','open','closed','','72-autosave-v1','','','2014-06-17 17:08:55','2014-06-17 21:08:55','',72,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/72-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
