	(532,3,'2014-10-09 14:04:13','2014-10-09 18:04:13','Brenda recently graduated in March of 2014 and jumped right into working at Fantastic Sams in Clifton Park. She loves all that Fantastic Sams has to offer. Brenda is taking full advantage of the education and is learning from her co-workers everyday. At Fantastic Sams there is a lot of room to grow and Brenda has already been promoted to Co-Manager in addition to being a stylist.\r\n\r\nBrenda has many fond memories of The Orlo. Brenda was very proud that she enjoyed perming at school because her very first client at Fantastic Sams was a piggyback perm, which she rocked! She misses working on the clinic floor with Ms. Jackie and with all of the friends she made along the way. During her time here, Brenda was willing to take on any client with a smile. Brenda is the proud mother of four children and works very hard to provide for her family.\r\n\r\nAnother Orlo graduate, Ashley, has also joined the ranks of Fantastic Sams in Clifton Park. Ashley is a 2013 graduate and is fairly new to the Fantastic Sams salon. She enjoys working there because of the convenience of the walk-ins and meeting new clients daily. She is quickly learning the Chi color line and enjoys taking men’s and women’s haircuts.\r\n\r\nAshley agrees with Brenda that you make lifelong friends at The Orlo. She was happy to have a great support system of friends while she completed her cosmetology course and had a lot of fun along the way! Ashley misses Mrs. Craw and all of her funny stories. She felt like Mrs. Craw really prepared her for the NYS Cosmetology Board Exams.\r\n\r\nWay to go Brenda and Ashley and we wish you much continued success!','Alumni Spotlight: Brenda Beauregard and Ashley Bevis ','','publish','open','closed','','alumni-spotlight-brenda-beauregard-ashley-bevis','','','2014-10-09 14:11:26','2014-10-09 18:11:26','',0,'http://www.theorloschool.com/?p=532',0,'post','',0),
	(538,3,'2014-10-21 15:15:19','2014-10-21 19:15:19','We had the opportunity to catch up with three graduates at <strong>Changes Salon</strong> in Latham, New York. Changes is a beautiful salon owned by stylist Joe Green and has a wonderful assistant program where graduates are nurtured to grow.\r\n\r\nFirst up, <strong>Elke Farinacci</strong>, is a 2008 graduate who has been at Changes since July 2013. Elke grew up in the industry, with her mother (our very own Mrs. Siebels) who owned Cuts and Such in Troy, New York.   Elke and her sisters played “tanning salon”, swept floors and would greet customers! After graduating high school, Elke was focused on going to college and entered into nursing school. After a couple years of college under her belt, Elke decided to turn her career goals into cosmetology.\r\n\r\nElke had a great time while at The Orlo School. She advises current students to make the most of school, make new friends and get ready to work hard! You need to lay the foundation and understand the basics.\r\n\r\nElke loves Changes for many reasons most importantly because it is a great place to grow and learn. Every Thursday, the salon participates in education where they learn from each other, the owner or different instructional videos. Elke said, ”Why would I ever say no to education, knowing what it costs outside of the salon.”\r\n\r\nA piece of advice Elke shares with current students, “In order to be successful, be your best. There are salons on every corner and you want to work where you love.” Thank you, Elke! We wish you much continued success.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur next graduate, <strong>Leah Quinn</strong>, is a 2013 graduate who has been working at Changes since January 2014. Leah has never been happier since joining Changes. After graduating with a Bachelor’s Degree from UAlbany in Communications, Leah didn’t really find a passion until she started at The Orlo.\r\n\r\nLeah says that she took a little bit of a longer path to get into cosmetology but appreciates how every experience in life shapes you into what you are. She felt mature and focused when she started at The Orlo. Leah juggled working full time and going to school full time but she said it was “definitely worth it.” She loved her time at The Orlo where she misses seeing all her teachers and friends in the morning. Leah also felt completely prepared for the State Board exams.\r\n\r\nStarting as an assistant, Leah was responsible for everything! She currently assists twice a week and takes clients three times a week. Leah loves the educational opportunities at Changes. She has trained at the Keune Academy in Atlanta and has traveled to Rochester for additional training.\r\n\r\nLeah takes pride in her work and loves a neat and polished look that coincides with her classic style. Bravo Leah! Best of luck to you!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur final graduate, <strong>Sandy Smith</strong>, is a very recent graduate completing the course in June 2014. Sandy is a part time assistant at Changes in addition to being a Teachers Aide in Cohoes City School District. Sandy was a client of Changes and knew she wanted to work there after she graduated. Sandy loves doing hair and would eventually love to do it full time.\r\n\r\nSandy worked hard building a portfolio and resume while she was at The Orlo and had an interview with Changes lined up before she graduated. She loves the in-house training on Thursdays especially with Joe. She has been learning a lot and loves learning a new color line.\r\n\r\nSandy misses her buddy Miss. Brown and offers some advice to current students, “Go to school everyday and ask for help.” Congratulations on your new career Sandy and enjoy the ride!','Alumni Spotlight: Elke Farinacci, Leah Quinn and Sandy Smith','','publish','open','closed','','alumni-spotlight-elke-farinacci-leah-quinn-sandy-smith','','','2014-10-23 14:15:33','2014-10-23 18:15:33','',0,'http://www.theorloschool.com/?p=538',0,'post','',0),
	(516,3,'2014-10-02 09:34:25','2014-10-02 13:34:25','<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Brittany, a 2013 graduate of The Orlo is a stylist at Hair Studio One in Glenmont.  She has been styling hair at this salon since March and loves it!  As a well-rounded stylist, Brittany specializes in cut and color.  Hair Studio One offers their stylists education in areas of color, cutting, product knowledge and business.  She takes advantage of these classes and loves working with Goldwell color.  Working at Hair Studio One allows Brittany to meet new people and accommodate walk ins all while working in a friendly atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As a fairly new stylist, Brittany offers some advice for recent graduates…. “Do not be afraid to jump right in after you graduate because once you do, it’s very easy!”  Brittany enjoys running promotions on services and products to help build her clientele.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Brittany misses her Orlo Family especially Mrs. Craw, Mrs. Siebels and her buddy Andrew.  She is thankful that The Orlo prepared her for the state board exams and happy for the people she met along the way!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Bravo Brittany!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>','Alumni Spotlight: Brittany Ambrosano','','publish','open','closed','','alumni-spotlight-brittany-ambrosano','','','2014-10-02 09:42:33','2014-10-02 13:42:33','',0,'http://www.theorloschool.com/?p=516',0,'post','',0),
