	(443,1,'2014-06-27 12:18:13','2014-06-27 16:18:13','What drew Alice to the cosmetology industry? “It was the creative aspect of it and being able to work with my hands in a friendly atmosphere where they played good music all of the time. The salon atmosphere is the best.” With experience in the industry since 1978, Alice worked in salons and as a beauty school instructor before becoming a director of former sister school Colonna in 1989 then an owner/director of Orlo in 1995.\n\nShe loves seeing new people find a profession in which they can feel comfortable and can grow. It’s rewarding. Cosmetology is a journey and it’s always changing. You’re always learning new things and meeting new people, and she loves every minute of it.','Alice Caputo','Director/Owner','inherit','open','closed','','74-autosave-v1','','','2014-06-27 12:18:13','2014-06-27 16:18:13','',74,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/74-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(444,1,'2014-06-27 12:19:31','2014-06-27 16:19:31','Whether you’re graduating high school now or trying to attend cosmetology school despite your current job keeping you busy, we know a weekday education schedule isn’t for everyone. At The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology, you can find the cosmetology classes you need held during weekdays, nights and weekends.\r\n\r\nOur full-time day, full-time evening and part-time evening programs provide students the flexibility they need to complete their studies on-time and on-budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Day: </strong>\r\nMonday through Friday, 8:45 a.m. to 3:15 p.m.\r\n30 hours per week, approximately 34 to 36 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Full-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\nSaturday: 9:00 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.\r\n25 hours per week, approximately 40 to 43 weeks\r\n\r\n<strong>Part-time Evening:\r\n</strong>Monday through Thursday, 5:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m.\r\n20 hours per week, approximately 50 to 54 weeks\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Tuition &amp; Financial Aid\" href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//admissions/tuition-financial-aid/\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition</a> is the same regardless of the program schedule you choose - we want you to choose the schedule that will provide you the opportunity to succeed!\r\n\r\n[accordion title=\"School Holidays\"] No classes are scheduled at Orlo on the following days each year:\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>New Year’s Day</li>\r\n	<li>Martin Luther King Day</li>\r\n	<li>Presidents’ Day</li>\r\n	<li>Memorial Day</li>\r\n	<li>Fourth of July (entire week)</li>\r\n	<li>Labor Day</li>\r\n	<li>Columbus Day</li>\r\n	<li>Veterans Day</li>\r\n	<li>Thanksgiving (two days)</li>\r\n	<li>Christmas (one week)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/accordion][accordion title=\"Unexpected Closures\"] In cases of circumstances such as weather and natural disasters, school closure announcements will be available on our website. Additional notifications will be made by personal phone call, radio/TV announcements or on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/theorloschool\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a> as applicable.\r\n[/accordion]','Course Schedule','','inherit','open','closed','','126-revision-v1','','','2014-06-27 12:19:31','2014-06-27 16:19:31','',126,'http://www.theorloschool.com//2014/06/126-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
