	(528,3,'2014-10-02 10:43:55','2014-10-02 14:43:55','Andrew was born into the beauty industry. Having grown up in Albany at The Orlo school of Hair Design &amp; Cosmetology, being a hairstylist was low on his list of passions and career ambitions. It wasn\'t until he started working full time at the school that he realized the impact of the beauty industry. \"<em>Beauty changes lives</em>, and it has certainly changed mine. Ever since I started working at Orlo, I\'ve become a whole new person. I was one of the shyest kids growing up. Being in this industry quickly changed that, as it truly brings you out of your shell. Hairstylists touch peoples\' lives, we give people a sense of self confidence through the power of appearance enhancement. When you look good, you feel good. Everyone excels when they feel good!\" Andrew eventually enrolled in Orlo\'s cosmetology course and became a licensed cosmetologist in September 2011. \"I look forward to being the future of my parents\' long history and keeping up the tradition of the family business here at Orlo.\"','Andrew Caputo','Director of Operations/Owner','inherit','open','closed','','205-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-02 10:43:55','2014-10-02 14:43:55','',205,'http://www.theorloschool.com/2014/10/205-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(529,3,'2014-10-02 11:05:25','2014-10-02 15:05:25','Rick is the “patriarch” of the Orlo family. His first introduction to the beauty industry was in the early 1960s, when he drove his Aunt Carmey to beauty school from Gloversville to Albany everyday. Was it all the pretty women, or was it the energy and excitement of the business that intrigued him the most? From that time on, he was hooked. After gaining experience in the salon as a licensed cosmetologist, he became engrossed in teaching cosmetology. At the time, Sassoon was becoming a household name, and Leo Passage was revolutionizing the way cosmetology was taught with his scientific approach to hairdressing. The industry was going through a transformation, and Rick was at the forefront. He became a platform artist for the Clairol Company and won numerous awards for his hair-cutting and hair-styling skills. He also trained several of his students to compete in local and national styling competitions.\n\nOver the years, Rick has learned the “ins and outs” of the beauty school business and all that the industry entails. Thousands of successful cosmetologists have graduated from his schools. After marrying Alice in 1984, they went into the beauty school business together, first with Colonna Beauty School where Rick had worked since the early 1960s. In 1995, they purchased The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology to provide a more convenient location for their students. Rick is now grooming his children, Angela and Andrew to hone their skills to carry on the tradition to the next generation. “Hairdressing and cosmetology have always been my passion. I take great pride in our many accomplished students who have gone on to have their own successful careers in the industry.”','Rick Caputo','President/CEO/Owner','inherit','open','closed','','72-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-02 11:05:25','2014-10-02 15:05:25','',72,'http://www.theorloschool.com/2014/10/72-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(530,3,'2014-10-02 12:12:00','2014-10-02 16:12:00','The Orlo School of Hair Design and Cosmetology offers tools and guidance inside the classroom and through one-on-one counseling to shape meaningful employment experiences, assisting students in engaging their passions and achieving their goals. Orlo\'s staff members assist students with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>State Board prep days</li>\r\n	<li>State Board workshops</li>\r\n	<li>Résumé development</li>\r\n	<li>Cover letter development</li>\r\n	<li>Employment portfolio development</li>\r\n	<li>Job interview preparation</li>\r\n	<li>Networking</li>\r\n	<li>Job placement assistance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition, our cosmetology <a title=\"Curriculum\" href=\"http://www.theorloschool.com//program/curriculum/\" target=\"_blank\">curriculum</a> covers the following sections of Milady Cosmetology\'s Business Skills Course within our classrooms:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seeking Employment</li>\r\n	<li>On the Job</li>\r\n	<li>The Salon Business</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>When should a student begins looking for a job - while they are still studying or after?</h4>\r\nExplore potential opportunities while attending school. Do not wait until graduation to begin your search. If you do, you may be tempted to take the first offer you receive. Research salon websites and social media accounts that interest you. Look for the salon that will be best for you and your goals. When you\'ve identified one or more salons that interest you, create and finalize your cover letter, résumé and references.\r\n<h4>How should students approach looking for their first job in the cosmetology industry?</h4>\r\nExplore the job market and research potential employers. Ask yourself:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What do you really want out of a career in cosmetology?</li>\r\n	<li>What particular areas within the beauty industry are the most interesting to you?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThen take action. Explore the job market and research potential employers. Get out there - network! Visit salons and talk to their owners, managers, educators and stylists.','Career Placement','','inherit','open','closed','','128-revision-v1','','','2014-10-02 12:12:00','2014-10-02 16:12:00','',128,'http://www.theorloschool.com/2014/10/128-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(533,3,'2014-10-09 13:58:07','2014-10-09 17:58:07','Brenda recently graduated in March of 2014 and jumped right into working at Fantastic Sams in Clifton Park. She loves all that Fantastic Sams has to offer. Brenda is taking full advantage of the education and is learning from her co-workers everyday. At Fantastic Sams there is a lot of room to grow and Brenda has already been promoted to Co-Manager in addition to being a stylist.\r\n\r\nBrenda has many fond memories of The Orlo. Brenda was very proud that she enjoyed perming at school because her very first client at Fantastic Sams was a piggyback perm, which she rocked! She misses working on the clinic floor with Ms. Jackie and with all of the friends she made along the way. During her time here, Brenda was willing to take on any client with a smile. Brenda is the proud mother of four children and works very hard to provide for her family.\r\n\r\nAnother Orlo graduate, Ashley, has also joined the ranks of Fantastic Sams in Clifton Park. Ashley is a 2013 graduate and is fairly new to the Fantastic Sams salon. She enjoys working there because of the convenience of the walk-ins and meeting new clients daily. She is quickly learning the Chi color line and enjoys taking men’s and women’s haircuts.\r\n\r\nAshley agrees with Brenda that you make lifelong friends at The Orlo. She was happy to have a great support system of friends while she completed her cosmetology degree and had a lot of fun along the way. Ashley misses Mrs. Craw and all of her funny stories. She felt like Mrs. Craw really prepared her for the NYS Cosmetology Board Exams.\r\n\r\nWay to go Brenda and Ashley and we wish you much continued success!','Alumni Spotlight: Brenda Beauregard and Ashley Bevis ','','inherit','open','closed','','532-revision-v1','','','2014-10-09 13:58:07','2014-10-09 17:58:07','',532,'http://www.theorloschool.com/2014/10/532-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(534,3,'2014-10-09 14:00:51','2014-10-09 18:00:51','Brenda recently graduated in March of 2014 and jumped right into working at Fantastic Sams in Clifton Park. She loves all that Fantastic Sams has to offer. Brenda is taking full advantage of the education and is learning from her co-workers everyday. At Fantastic Sams there is a lot of room to grow and Brenda has already been promoted to Co-Manager in addition to being a stylist.\r\n\r\nBrenda has many fond memories of The Orlo. Brenda was very proud that she enjoyed perming at school because her very first client at Fantastic Sams was a piggyback perm, which she rocked! She misses working on the clinic floor with Ms. Jackie and with all of the friends she made along the way. During her time here, Brenda was willing to take on any client with a smile. Brenda is the proud mother of four children and works very hard to provide for her family.\r\n\r\nAnother Orlo graduate, Ashley, has also joined the ranks of Fantastic Sams in Clifton Park. Ashley is a 2013 graduate and is fairly new to the Fantastic Sams salon. She enjoys working there because of the convenience of the walk-ins and meeting new clients daily. She is quickly learning the Chi color line and enjoys taking men’s and women’s haircuts.\r\n\r\nAshley agrees with Brenda that you make lifelong friends at The Orlo. She was happy to have a great support system of friends while she completed her cosmetology course and had a lot of fun along the way! Ashley misses Mrs. Craw and all of her funny stories. She felt like Mrs. Craw really prepared her for the NYS Cosmetology Board Exams.\r\n\r\nWay to go Brenda and Ashley and we wish you much continued success!','Alumni Spotlight: Brenda Beauregard and Ashley Bevis ','','inherit','open','closed','','532-revision-v1','','','2014-10-09 14:00:51','2014-10-09 18:00:51','',532,'http://www.theorloschool.com/2014/10/532-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
